  "texts": [
    "In order to implement this symmetry on O q, we need to make a choice of a topological defect lying at the intersection of O q and the symmetry generator D d-1.",
    "We can either choose this topological defect to be D(i) q-1 or D (-i) q-1.Let us make the choice D (i) q-1 without loss of generality.",
    "Now we check whether the symmetry is still 2 valued by performing the fusion of these topological defects.",
    "As we fuse D d-1 with itself, it becomes a trivial defect, which means the symmetry is 2 -valued in the bulk.",
    "However along the worldvolume of O q we have to fuse D (i) q-1 with itself, resulting in the generator of the 2 symmetry localized along O q D (i)q-1 ⊗ D (i) q-1 = D (-) q-1."
  ],
